#!/usr/bin/env python
"""
CESMLC V6 - Problem-state seed-label dataset builder
====================================================

Purpose
-------
Build a model-ready, weak/semi-supervised training dataset from CESMLC LTE audit history.

V6 is intentionally different from the older broad source-change detector:

1. Candidate gate is latest-day DB_MISMATCH='YES'.
2. The main evidence is 30-day SOURCE history for candidate ECGIs only.
3. FEATURE_DB columns are NOT used for the whole detection model.
4. FEATURE_DB columns can optionally be used only for a narrow, separate
   AUDIT_PUSH_NOT_APPLIED seed/check, because that problem type is inherently
   source-vs-server/DB behavior.
5. Outputs include high-precision seed labels, suppressor labels, confidence,
   training weights, and a manual-review feedback template.

Install once if needed:
    python -m pip install duckdb pandas numpy

Safe example
------------
python cesmlc_v6_seed_label_dataset_builder.py ^
  --input "C:\\Temp\\enmt_cesmlc_lte_audit_p_akr3aesme01_30d.csv" ^
  --days 30 ^
  --out-dir "C:\\Temp\\cesmlc_v6_seed_akr3aesme01_30d_outputs" ^
  --include-features "PHYSICALCELLID,CELLNAME,CELLTYPE,ANTENNALAT,ANTENNALON,ANTENNAORIENTATION,ANTENNAOPENING,ANTENNAHORIZONTALRANGE,ANTENNABASEALTITUDE,GEOTYPE,RADIUS1,SRVNGAREAAVERAGEALT,SRVNGAREAAVGALTUNCERT,SUPPORTEDTECHNOLOGIES" ^
  --defaults-json "C:\\Temp\\cesmlc_v6_feature_rules_template.json" ^
  --latlon-decimals 5 ^
  --memory-limit 6GB ^
  --threads 1 ^
  --feature-batch-size 1 ^
  --duckdb-temp-dir "C:\\Temp\\duckdb_spill_v6"

Optional narrow DB push check:
    add --enable-db-push-check
"""

